One of the first models to break away from its usual conservative styling roots, the Toyota C-HR has, since going on sale in South Africa three years ago, been something of a quiet entity as the segment it competes in exploded at a rapid rate. Undeniably a niche model skewed more towards the sporty side of the compact SUV market rather than a fully-fledged volume seeker, the youthful and funky Coupe High-Rider has now benefited from a mid-life facelift that not only brings a few cosmetic enhancements, but also new comfort and safety features. Arguably one of the few models...